CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1953, pg. 16, reads: "OFF TO INAUGURATION - Among the politicians who left Pittsburgh on two trains Monday to attend the inaugural ceremonies in Washington, D.C., were Emory Sellers, controller for the Allegheny County Republican executive committee; Curtis B. Haines, Workmen's Compensation Referee and Fifth Ward Republican chairman; Alvin E. Dillman, Workmen's Compensation Referee and chairman of the "Inauguration Special" committee; Irving Johnson, proprietor of the Flamingo Hotel, and B. B. Epstein, owner of Eppy's Parking Lot. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Emory Sellers, Curtis B. Haines, Alvin E. Dillman, Irving Johnson, and B. B. Epstein standing in front of Pennsylvanian train, before traveling to Washington D.C. for Eisenhower and Nixon inauguration, another version
